The TDD exercise is complete. Here's a summary of what was built:

**Files created:**
- `src/game-of-life.ts` — Core Game of Life logic with sparse representation
- `src/game-of-life.spec.ts` — 7 tests covering all base functionality
- `src/cli.ts` — CLI entry point reading JSON from stdin, writing JSON to stdout

**Key design decisions through TDD:**
- `Cell = [number, number]` type alias (extracted during refactor)
- `cellKey` helper for position string encoding (DRY refactor)
- `byPosition` comparator (DRY refactor — was duplicated)
- `livesOn` predicate naming Conway's survival rules (intent refactor)
- Sparse neighbor counting via `Map<string, number>` — only tracks candidate positions, handles negative coordinates naturally
- Lexicographic sort applied to all output paths (zero-steps and N-steps)
